            <section class="article-chapter">
                <div class="chapter-number">03</div>
                <h2 class="chapter-title">The Challenge for Indian Investors</h2>
                <p class="article-text">Trading US stocks from India isn't as simple as trading Reliance or Infosys.
                    Here's what you're up against:</p>
                <div class="warning-box">
                    <h4><i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle"></i> Barriers to US Stock Trading</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Currency Conversion:</strong> Every trade involves INR ‚Üí USD conversion with hidden
                            spreads</li>
                        <li><strong>Time Zone Hell:</strong> US markets open 7:00 PM IST (summer) or 8:30 PM IST
                            (winter)</li>
                        <li><strong>Tax Complications:</strong> Both Indian AND US tax applies (15% TDS in US + capital
                            gains in India)</li>
                        <li><strong>RBI Limits:</strong> $250,000 per year under LRS (Liberalized Remittance Scheme)
                        </li>
                        <li><strong>Higher Fees:</strong> International brokers charge more than domestic ones</li>
                        <li><strong>Fractional Shares Confusion:</strong> Not all brokers offer fractional shares
                            (buying 0.1 Tesla instead of 1 full share)</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <p class="article-text">But don't worry. The right broker solves most of these problems. Let's find
                    yours.</p>
            </section> <!-- Top 8 Brokers Comparison -->
